off values and longer lived in\nweaker flares and flares with a more gradual energy deposition timescale. These\nresults demonstrate the usefulness of orthohelium line emission as a diagnostic\nof flare energy transport.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 30 Mar 2021 21:18:22 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 23 May 2021 18:20:45 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-05-26"}
