e varies with stellar\nevolution. This provides us with a physical basis for distinguishing red giant\nbranch stars from asymptotic giants. Here, our investigation of stellar\noscillations allows us to constrain the physical processes and the key events\nthat occur during the advanced stages of stellar evolution, with emphasis on\nthe ascent along the asymptotic giant branch, including the asymptotic giant\nbranch bump.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 30 Mar 2021 23:11:59 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-06-16"}
